The paper discusses the use of analog codes in multi-level memory systems, which involves the encoding and decoding of analog signals. This topic falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT), which deals with the study of communication systems and their limits. The paper also discusses the use of phase change memory as a prototypical multi-level storage technology, which falls under the field of computer architecture (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of signal statistics, device statistics, and a distortion metric, which falls under the fields of electrical engineering (cs.ET) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for analog memory systems to be more energy efficient, which falls under the field of emerging technologies (cs.EM).
